               <head>Persian translation of Chaghnini's treatise on astronomy</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Ghiyās̲īyah by Maḥmūd ibn Muḥammad Haravī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2009116093 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85068424 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh90002170" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Or_16420-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>A rare brief treatise on astronomy, completed in 803/1400-1, by Maḥmūd ibn Muḥammad Haravī, who was apparently vizier to Shah Rukh. Essentially a translation of <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_71009882" ref="http://lccn.loc.gov/n2005181552" role="ant">Chaghmīnī</persName>’s Arabic treatise <title>al-Mulakhkhaṣ fī l-hay’a</title>, Ghiyāsiyya comprises a muqaddima and two maqālas. It is dedicated (henced the title) to Ghiyās al-Dīn Sayyid Aḥmad Haravī.
                        </p>
                        <p>For details on Ghiyāsiyya, see FNKhF I, p. 331, which lists only three manuscripts. Muḥammad ibn Maḥmūd Haravī does not appear in Storey, PL, which does however include two Persian commentaries on Chaghmīnī (see PL II/1 E, p. 50. For Chaghmīnī and his Mulakhkhaṣ see Storey, loc. cit.; Brockelmann, GAL I, p. 473 and S I, p. 865.</p>
                        <p>Begins:
Basmala  Sipās-i nā-ma‘dūd va sitāyash-i nā-maḥdūd Āfarīdagārī-rāst ki tadvīr-i davāyir-i tis‘a aflāk ... Chunīn gūyad muḥarrir-i īn maqāla va muqarrir-i īn risāla
</p>
                        <p>Ends:
Va īn sāl az sāl-i shamsī-i ḥaqīqī kamtarast ba-dah rūz va has[h]t sā‘at va nīm ba-taqrīb  Va LLāh a‘lam ... Ba-amr-i Khwāja-’i Āfāq Āṣaf-i sānī ... Ghiyās-i Dawlat va Dīn ... házih al-kitāb (sic) Mulḥaq Chaghmīnī min taṣnīf Mullā ‘Alī al-Kāshifī raḥmat Allāh ‘alayh
</p>
                        <p>Undated: ca. 10th-11th/16th-17th century. </p>
                        <p>Clear nasta‘līq. 13 lines. Red headings. Thin off-white paper; some light worming. 58 folios. 195 x 149 mm.; text lines 134 x 87 mm. Worn half red goatskin covers, faced with pink and blue marbled paper.</p>
                        <p>Purchased from M Moin, 30 August 2007.</p>
